## Debian Common Core Alliance

Ian Murdock of the DCCA asks what remains wrong. Branden Robinson advises him
that DCCA cannot use the Debian Open Use Logo as their name is no longer
Debian.

Benj. Mako Hill suggests that DCCA seek a trademark license from Debian.
Murdock advises that this idea has been dismissed out of hand by DCCA.

The discussion is ultimately referred back to Debian for resolution.


## OFTC update

