## DUS

Ian Jackson moves that `The SPI Board notes that MJ Ray has been shit-stirring
about Debian UK and asks him to stop doing so.' The motion is not seconded.

Debian UK is embroiled in controversy over automatically considering UK Debian
developers members. Some members consider this a violation of human rights and
would like to see the trademark license for DUS' use of Debian revoked.

Branden Robinson, speaking in his capacity as the Debian Project Leader,
states:

> My opinion is that: 1) If DUS automatically considers anyone
> a member of their Society by virtue of a UK resident becoming
> a Debian Developer, I request that that practice cease.

The discussion lasts twenty minutes and is deferred.


